# SCSS Standards

## Design Tokens

| Requirement                                  | Details                                                                          |
| -------------------------------------------- | -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| **Use design tokens**                        | Colors from `--color-*`, spacing from `--spacing-*`                              |
| **No hardcoded colors**                      | Always use CSS custom properties                                                 |
| **No hardcoded spacing**                     | Use `--spacing-*` tokens                                                         |

---

## Focus & Interaction States

| Requirement                                  | Details                                                                          |
| -------------------------------------------- | -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| **Focus states**                             | Use `[data-focus-visible]` for keyboard-only outlines                            |
| **Hover states**                             | Use `&:hover` with appropriate token colors                                      |
| **Disabled states**                          | Use `[data-disabled]` or `&:disabled`                                            |

---

## CSS Modules

| Requirement                                  | Details                                                                          |
| -------------------------------------------- | -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| **Avoid `:global`**                          | CSS modules should stay scoped                                                   |
| **Use `classnames`**                         | Not template literals for conditional classes                                    |

---

## Code Style

| Requirement                                  | Details                                                                          |
| -------------------------------------------- | -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| **Use mixins**                               | Extract repeated size/state patterns into `@mixin` instead of duplicating        |
| **Pill border-radius**                       | Use `9999px` for safety                                                          |
| **Pseudo-element order**                     | Put `content: ''` first                                                          |
| **Logical property order**                   | Position, then box model, then visual                                            |
| **No comments in SCSS**                      | In 99% of cases they are redundant; only for genuinely complex constructions     |
| **No `!important`**                          | Clean components never need it; if you think you do, refactor the selectors      |
| **Standard transition duration**             | Use `0.2s` as the standard transition duration across components                 |
| **Component-scoped variables**               | Keep component-specific CSS variables in the component file, not in `_root.scss` |

---

## Examples

```scss
// Good
.button {
  color: var(--color-text-primary);
  padding: var(--spacing-2) var(--spacing-4);
  border-radius: var(--radius-md);
  transition: background-color 0.2s;

  &:hover {
    background-color: var(--color-bg-hover);
  }

  &[data-focus-visible] {
    outline: 2px solid var(--color-focus);
    outline-offset: 2px;
  }

  &[data-disabled] {
    opacity: 0.5;
    cursor: not-allowed;
  }
}

.pill {
  border-radius: 9999px;
}

.icon::before {
  content: '';
  display: block;
  width: 16px;
  height: 16px;
}
```

```scss
// Bad
.button {
  color: #333;
  padding: 8px 16px;
  transition: all 0.3s;

  &:focus {
    outline: 2px solid blue !important;
  }
}

:global(.external-class) {
  color: red;
}
```

```scss
// Good - extract repeated patterns into mixins
@mixin avatar-size($size, $font-size) {
  width: $size;
  height: $size;
  font-size: $font-size;
}

.small {
  @include avatar-size(24px, var(--font-size-xs));
}

.medium {
  @include avatar-size(32px, var(--font-size-sm));
}

// Bad - duplicated size declarations
.small {
  width: 24px;
  height: 24px;
  font-size: var(--font-size-xs);
}

.medium {
  width: 32px;
  height: 32px;
  font-size: var(--font-size-sm);
}
```
